def plot_hist(ax=None, series=None, bins=50, density=True):
    mean = series.mean(); mode = series.mode()[0]
    ax = ax or plt.gca()
    
    hist = sns.histplot(series, bins=bins, kde=True, linewidth=0, ax=ax)
    heights = [patch.get_height() for patch in ax.patches]; max_height = max(heights)
    ax.axvline(mean, color='black', ls='--')
    ax.axvline(mode, color='blue', ls='--')
    ax.text(mean+mean/50, max_height/3, f'$\mu_e\ =\ {mean:.2f}\ $')
    ax.text(mode+mode/50, max_height/4, f'$\mu_o\ =\ {mode:.2f}\ $', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel(f'{units[series.name]}'); ax.set_ylabel('');
    ax.set_title(f'  \n{series.name}')
       
    return hist

def plot_hist_and_box(series, bins=50, density=True):
    _, (ax0, ax1) = plt.subplots(1, 2, gridspec_kw={'width_ratios': [4, 1]}, figsize=figsize)
    plot_hist(ax0, series, bins=bins, density=density)
    ax1.boxplot(series)
    ax1.set_title(f'   \n{series.name}');
    ax1.set_xlabel(series.name); ax1.set_ylabel(units[series.name])

    
def plot_hists_and_boxes(df, hist_grid_shape, box_grid_shape, density=True, bins=50):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(figsize[0], figsize[1]*hist_grid_shape[0]/2+figsize[1]*box_grid_shape[0]))
    outer = gridspec.GridSpec(2, 1, right=1.5, top=1.1, height_ratios=[hist_grid_shape[0], box_grid_shape[0]])
    hist_inner = gridspec.GridSpecFromSubplotSpec(*hist_grid_shape, subplot_spec=outer[0], hspace=0.4)
    box_inner = gridspec.GridSpecFromSubplotSpec(*box_grid_shape, subplot_spec=outer[1], wspace=0.5)

    for i, col_name in enumerate(df.columns):
        ax0 = plt.Subplot(fig, hist_inner[i])
        ax1 = plt.Subplot(fig, box_inner[i])
        plot_hist(ax0, df[col_name], density=density, bins=bins)
        ax1.boxplot(df[col_name].dropna())
        ax1.set_title(f'{col_name}')
        ax1.set_ylabel(units[col_name])
        fig.add_subplot(ax0)
        fig.add_subplot(ax1)

In[83]:
def finetune(model_name, parameters, features, target, verbose=3, jobs=-1, cv=5, **kwargs):
    '''  
        ,    ,    
        ,         MAE
    '''
    cv = GridSearchCV(model_name(**kwargs), param_grid=parameters, scoring='neg_mean_absolute_error',
                            cv=cv, verbose=verbose, n_jobs=jobs)
    cv.fit(features, target)  
    
    return cv.best_estimator_, cv.best_params_, -cv.best_score_

def print_cv_results(params, metric):
    '''  -  '''
    print()
    print(f'  : {params}')
    print(f'(train, CV)  MAE: {metric:.4f} ')
    print()
